"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390487","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-20","<p /> <p>Ministers had regard to all relevant international obligations when formulating the welfare policies announced at the Budget and consider that these obligations have been complied with.</p><p> </p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","7379 ; 7380","2015-07-20T16:24:50.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390487/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390487/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390487/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-15","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment his Department has made of the compatibility of changes to (a) the benefit cap and (b) housing benefits with the European Convention on Human Rights.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","7378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390488","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-20","<p /> <p>To prevent young people slipping straight into a life on benefits, from April 2017 the Government will remove the automatic entitlement to housing support for new claims in Universal Credit from 18-21 year olds who are out of work. This will ensure young people in the benefits system face the same choices as young people who work and who may not be able to afford to leave home.</p><p> </p><p>We will ensure that vulnerable young people who are in need of support for their housing needs continue to receive it. Government will consider the impact in line with our legal obligations as part of that process.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-20T14:55:23.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390488/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390488/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390488/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-15","Housing Benefit: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what plans he has to provide for exemptions for young people who cannot live with their parents from the removal of housing benefit for 18 to 21 year olds.","false","Biography information for Sir Charles Walker","Broxbourne","Mr Charles Walker","7370"
