"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389728","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-20","<p>Treasury Ministers have meetings and discussions with a wide variety of organisations as part of the policy development and delivery process. A record of Ministerial meetings is published and updated periodically on the government website at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-07-20T13:45:36.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389728/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389728/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389728/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-14","Treasury: Tobacco","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many times (a) he and (b) other Ministers in his Department met employees or third-party representatives of tobacco companies in (i) 2013, (ii) 2014 and (iii) 2015.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","7011"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389729","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-20","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) seek to recover all overpayments of tax credits no matter how they have arisen, as they do with all debts.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>However, HMRC error accounts for only 1.4% of overpayments.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-07-20T15:43:36.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389729/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389729/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389729/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-14","Welfare Tax Credits: Overpayments","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether his plans to extend the use of the private sector to improve the collection of tax credit debt will target recipients who have been overpaid due to HM Revenue and Customs error.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","7001"
