"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389183","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-24","<p>The British Government remains concerned about the growing threat from extremist groups in Libya, including those affiliated with the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL). We have seen barbaric and appalling acts of terror inside Libya, including the brutal murders of Egyptian Coptic Christians and Ethiopian Christians. We are investigating possible links between ISIL in Libya and the recent terrorist attacks in Tunisia. We are working with Libya’s neighbours to enhance their capacity to tackle the threat.</p><p>A lasting and inclusive political settlement and the establishment of a Government of National Accord (GNA) is the best way to tackle the threat in the long term. We stand ready to support the GNA on security issues, not least tackling ISIL, as soon as it is formed.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-07-24T11:47:08.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389183/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389183/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389183/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-13","Libya: Islamic State","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in light of the recent terrorist attack in Tunisia, what strategy they have to prevent the further expansion of IS in Libya.","false","Biography information for The Marquess of Lothian",,"The Marquess of Lothian","HL1369"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389184","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-24","<p>Ministers and officials have remained in regular contact with the Tunisian authorities since the attack in Sousse on 26 June. The Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond), spoke to Foreign Minister Baccouche on 27 June and Prime Minister Essid on 5 July. The Secretary of State for the Home Department, my right hon. Friend the Member for Maidenhead (Mrs May), met Interior Minister Gharsalli on 29 June alongside the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my hon. Friend the Member for Bournemouth East (Mr Ellwood), who had previously spoken to Mr Gharsalli on 26 June.</p><p>Our Ambassador to Tunisia spoke to Foreign Minister Baccouche on 27 June. He remained in regular contact with representatives of the Tunisian authorities including ministers between 5 and 9 July.</p><p>The Foreign Secretary spoke again to the Tunisian Prime Minister on 9 July as the Travel Advice change was being made.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-07-24T11:46:46.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389184/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389184/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389184/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-13","Tunisia: Terrorism","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what consultations took place with the government of Tunisia in advance of the most recent Foreign and Commonwealth Office travel advice for Tunisia being issued; and when those consultations took place.","false","Biography information for The Marquess of Lothian",,"The Marquess of Lothian","HL1370"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389185","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-24","<p>We, along with our international partners in Afghanistan, share a common vision for an Afghan-led and Afghan-owned political process to bring an end to many years of conflict. We welcome the talks on 7 July in Pakistan and will continue to work closely to provide what support we can to Afghanistan in their pursuit of a negotiated settlement.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-07-24T11:24:34.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389185/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389185/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389185/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-13","Afghanistan: Peace Negotiations","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what support or advice they have offered to assist the peace talks between the government of Afghanistan and the Taliban, further to the meeting in Islamabad on 7 July.","false","Biography information for The Marquess of Lothian",,"The Marquess of Lothian","HL1371"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389186","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-24","<p>The UK takes enforcement of sanctions seriously. Violating sanctions is a criminal offence that can carry a significant custodial sentence. We cannot comment on individual criminal cases or sanctions breaches.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-07-24T11:24:51.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389186/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389186/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389186/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-13","Russia: Sanctions","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what information they have on whether sanctions against Russia have been breached by (1) British companies, (2) other European Union companies, and (3) Asian companies, particularly in relation to the energy industry.","false","Biography information for The Marquess of Lothian",,"The Marquess of Lothian","HL1372"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389187","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-24","<p>The Forced Marriage Unit (FMU) provides a range of support and assistance in cases where British nationals are at risk of forced marriage in the UK or overseas. In 2014, the FMU gave advice or support related to a possible forced marriage in 1267 cases.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-07-24T11:25:02.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389187/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389187/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389187/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-13","Forced Marriage Unit","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many cases the Forced Marriage Unit was involved in, or gave support and advice to, in 2014.","false","Biography information for The Lord Bishop of St Albans",,"The Lord Bishop of St Albans","HL1373"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389188","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-24","<p>Not all forced marriage cases are reported to the British Government's Forced Marriage Unit (FMU), which makes it impossible to make an accurate assessment on how many British girls may have been sent abroad to marry.</p><p>British girls may be sent abroad to marry with their full consent in the form of an arranged marriage. If the girl does not have the right to say no this becomes a forced marriage. The UK is a world leader in tackling forced (and early) marriage. It is child abuse, domestic abuse and a form of violence against women and men and a serious abuse of human rights.</p><p>The FMU dealt with 1267 cases in 2014. 77% of cases dealt with by the FMU in 2014 involve an overseas element, which means the victim is at risk of, or has been, taken overseas.</p><p>The number of cases the FMU deals with does not represent the number of British girls (and boys) being sent overseas for a forced marriage, but the number of calls and emails initiating contact with the FMU about a victim or potential victim.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-07-24T11:25:51.99Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389188/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389188/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389188/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-13","Forced Marriage","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of how many British girls were sent abroad to marry in 2014.","false","Biography information for The Lord Bishop of St Albans",,"The Lord Bishop of St Albans","HL1374"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389189","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-24","<p>Not all forced marriage cases are reported to the British Government's Forced Marriage Unit (FMU), which makes it impossible to make an accurate assessment on how many underage British girls may have been sent abroad to marry.</p><p>The UK is a world leader in tackling forced (and early) marriage. It is child abuse, domestic abuse and a form of violence against women and men and a serious abuse of human rights.</p><p>The FMU dealt with 1267 cases in 2014. 77% of cases dealt with by the FMU in 2014 involve an overseas element, which means the victim is at risk of, or has been, taken overseas.</p><p>In 22% of cases dealt with by the FMU in 2014 the victim was under 18 years old. The number of cases the FMU deals with does not represent the number of underage British girls (and boys) being sent overseas for a forced marriage, but the number of calls and emails initiating contact with the FMU about a victim or potential victim.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-07-24T11:26:29.46Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389189/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389189/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389189/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-13","Forced Marriage","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of how many underage British girls were sent abroad to marry in 2014.","false","Biography information for The Lord Bishop of St Albans",,"The Lord Bishop of St Albans","HL1375"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389190","The Lord Chairman of Committees","false","2015-07-20","<p>The maximum amount of financial assistance available to opposition parties will be: £259,357 to the Liberal Democrat party in the period 8 May 2015 to 31 March 2016; and £577,871 to the Labour Party in the period 1 April 2015 to 31 March 2016. The amount given may be less, depending on claims.</p><p>For each subsequent year, the maximum amount for the previous year is increased by the percentage (if any) by which the retail prices index for the previous March has increased compared with the index for the March before that, and (if the resulting amount is not a whole number of pounds) rounded to the nearest pound. The full-year equivalents on which the calculation will be based are £288,525 for the Liberal Democrat party and the amount set out above for the Labour party.</p><p>Financial assistance is available to assist the Opposition, the second largest opposition party and the Convenor of the Cross-Bench Peers in carrying out their Parliamentary business.</p>",,"Lord Sewel",,"2015-07-20T12:17:38.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389190/answer","Biography information for Lord Sewel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389190/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389190/answer",,,,,"200",,"Chairman of Committees (HoL)","2015-07-13","Political Parties: Finance","2","House of Lords","To ask the Chairman of Committees how much Cranborne money will be given to (1) the Liberal Democrat Party, and (2) the Labour Party; and over what period of time.","false","Biography information for Lord Pearson of Rannoch",,"Lord Pearson of Rannoch","HL1376"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389191","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-27","<p>The Government has secured a deal that protects UK taxpayers from any risk from financing euro area bailouts now and in the future. This deal gives legal force to the commitment secured in 2010 that UK taxpayers would not be drawn into a euro area bailout. Under the European Financial Stability Mechanism (EFSM) short term financing agreement concluded on Friday 17 July, Greece’s IMF arrears have also been cleared.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley",,"2015-07-27T15:57:30.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389191/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389191/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389191/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-07-13","Loans: Greece","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what estimate they have made of the cost to the public purse of (1) arrangements made, and (2) proposed arrangements, to deal with the Greek financial crisis.","false","Biography information for Lord Higgins",,"Lord Higgins","HL1377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389192","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-24","<p>We pay close attention to the human rights situation in China, and are concerned by reports of the detention of a number of human rights lawyers since 9 July 2015. We believe that rule of law, good governance and a transparent legal system are vital underpinnings for stability and will continue to engage China on these issues.</p><p>We support the EU statement of 15 July, which said the detentions raised serious questions about China's commitment to strengthening the rule of law and called for the release of all those detained for seeking to protect rights provided by the Chinese Constitution.</p><p>We have raised our concerns about the ongoing restrictions on civil society activity in China, including with the Chinese authorities during the UK-China Human Rights Dialogue in April this year.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-07-24T11:48:18.983Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389192/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389192/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389192/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-13","China: Human Rights","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the circumstances surrounding the arrest of more than one hundred political activists and human rights lawyers in China on 11 July.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL1378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389193","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-24","<p>We are concerned by reports of the detention of a number of human rights lawyers and activists since 9 July. We are also deeply concerned that many of those detained cannot be contacted.</p><p> </p><p>We have regular discussions with the Chinese authorities, including on human rights and rule of law issues. We have raised our concerns about ongoing restrictions on civil society activity in China, including during the UK-China Human Rights Dialogue in April. We support the EU statement of 15 July on these detentions.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-07-24T11:26:54.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389193/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389193/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389193/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-13","China: Human Rights","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what information they have, and what representations they have made, about the arrest in China of human rights lawyers, including Li Fangping, and Christian lawyers, including Li Heping and Zhang Kai.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL1379"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389194","Department for International Development","false","2015-07-24","<p>The Department for International Development monitor the Famine Early Warning System (FEWS) reports and updates on a weekly basis. We also contribute to improving the methodology used for these assessments. FEWS produce many reports and cover many regions and countries, although not all of the countries at risk. When the risk of a significant worsening food security situation is reported by FEWS or others, DFID engages in a dialogue with other governments and with our operational partners on the best possible early response.</p><p>In places where we have a comparative advantage, such as countries where we have offices and an on-going bilateral programme, we fund food security, livelihood and nutrition interventions.</p><p>In countries most often at risk we also run resilience and food security programmes aimed at making communities more robust to future deterioration in food security or shocks such as droughts, floods and other natural disasters.</p>",,"Baroness Verma",,"2015-07-24T13:16:50.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389194/answer","Biography information for Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389194/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389194/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-07-13","Famine","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what steps they are taking to respond to the latest report by the Famine Early Warning System, which highlights the risk of worsening food security.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL1380"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389195","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-07-21","<p>Information on the change in the number of full time equivalent band 3 to 5 prison officers in Wandsworth between 31 May 2010 and 31 March 2015 is shown in the table below.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Table: Number of Full Time Equivalent Officers in Wandsworth, 31 May 2010 - 31 March 2015</strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Officer Grade</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>31 May 2010</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>31 March 2015</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>% Change</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Band 3-5 Officers</strong></p></td><td><p>420</p></td><td><p>270</p></td><td><p>-35</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>All figures are rounded to the nearest 10, with numbers ending in 5 rounded to the nearest multiple of 20 to prevent systematic bias. As with all HR databases, extracts are taken at a fixed point in time, to ensure consistency of reporting. The database itself is dynamic however, and where updates to the database are made subsequent to the taking of the extract, these updates will not be reflected in figures produced by the extract. For this reason, HR data are unlikely to be precisely accurate, and to present unrounded figures would be to overstate the accuracy of the figures. Rounding to 10 accurately depicts the level of certainty that is held with these figures.</p><p> </p><p>Percentages are formed from unrounded parts prior to rounding. For this reason, percentages may not equal the calculated percentages of rounded figures.</p><p> </p><p>Since 2010 Wandsworth has undergone benchmarking as part of the New Ways of Working Model. This has resulted in a number of roles (for example instructors, caterers and programme facilitators) previously carried out by prison officers being civilianised. In additional a vulnerable prisoners unit was re-rolled from Category B to Category C and a small number of dog handlers moved to regional control. The target staffing figure is in line with similar establishments.</p>",,"Lord Faulks",,"2015-07-21T15:40:49.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389195/answer","Biography information for Lord Faulks","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389195/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389195/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-07-13","Wandsworth Prison","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government by what percentage the number of prison officers at HMP Wandsworth has reduced since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Lord Kennedy of Southwark",,"Lord Kennedy of Southwark","HL1381"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389196","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-20","<p>This information is not held centrally. The department is currently developing a robust Single Living Accommodation allocation and management system which will be available in 2016.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2015-07-20T15:40:06.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389196/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389196/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389196/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-13","Military Bases: Catterick","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what percentage of the accommodation at Catterick Garrison is en-suite.","false","Biography information for Lord Kennedy of Southwark",,"Lord Kennedy of Southwark","HL1382"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389197","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-07-22","<p /> <p>HMP Wandsworth is a large, diverse London prison catering for approximately 1620 men and comprising two units, a B-category local prison and a C-category resettlement unit. The religious affiliation of these prisoners is similarly diverse and is supported by a large multi-faith chaplaincy team. Recent HMIP inspections of the prison have given positive reports of chaplaincy provision and access to religious services.</p><p> </p><p>The prison has a good range and quality of religious space that allows each faith group to meet regularly in suitable surroundings. These include a designated mosque, a church and two multi-faith chaplaincy rooms that are adaptable and used by the Sikh, Hindu, Buddhist, Jewish, Orthodox and Jehovah Witness faith communities.</p><p> </p><p>All prisoners are seen on arrival by the chaplaincy team and their religious affiliation ascertained. For the smaller faith groups, prisoners will be followed up by the individual chaplains and invited to a weekly time of worship. All faith groups have at least a minimum of one hour of weekly corporate worship and the offer of additional religious classes. For Christian and Muslim denominations, because of the substantial numbers involved, prisoners are asked to request whether they would like to attend a weekly time of worship.</p>",,"Lord Faulks",,"2015-07-22T15:30:30.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389197/answer","Biography information for Lord Faulks","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389197/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389197/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-07-13","Wandsworth Prison","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what facilities are available for prisoners at HMP Wandsworth to participate in acts of worship.","false","Biography information for Lord Kennedy of Southwark",,"Lord Kennedy of Southwark","HL1383"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389198","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-27","<p>The Government published analysis of the impact of government policy across the income distribution alongside the Summer Budget. This set out a new approach to distributional analysis, abstracting from the level of government borrowing. Under the previous framework, a pound of extra borrowing would appear as a gain to households. But higher spending or lower taxes today would increase the deficit and the debt burden, with consequences for households in the future. The new analysis considers how policy decisions affect the share of tax and public spending paid by and received by households.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The analysis showed that decisions made by this government mean the poorest continue to receive the same share of public spending as they did in 2010-11, while the share of tax paid by the richest has increased.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Publishing analysis for 2017-18 reflects a compromise between including as much of the Summer Budget package as possible, and making as few assumptions as possible about changes in the wider economy into the future. By 2017-18 the majority of announced welfare measures have come into effect, as have most of the significant changes to the tax system. Analysis for 2016-17 would capture very few of the measures announced in the Summer Budget; analysis from 2018-19 onwards, would need to make substantial assumptions about changes in household incomes and inflation.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley",,"2015-07-27T15:54:13.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389198/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389198/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389198/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-07-13","Budget July 2015","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government why they changed the basis of the distributional analysis of the most recent budget presented in <i>Impact on Households</i> from that in previous such documents, and whether they plan to publish (1) the analysis on the same basis as hitherto, and (2) estimates up to 2019–20.","false","Biography information for Baroness Lister of Burtersett",,"Baroness Lister of Burtersett","HL1384"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389199","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-27","<p>The information requested is not available, given that statistics on government spending do not break down expenditure by vulnerability.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley",,"2015-07-27T15:58:16.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389199/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389199/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389199/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-07-13","Public Expenditure","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government which groups of the population are classified as vulnerable for public expenditure purposes.","false","Biography information for Baroness Lister of Burtersett",,"Baroness Lister of Burtersett","HL1385"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389200","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-22","<p>In July 2014, the Secretary of State for Transport announced the next steps for delivering a new Lower Thames crossing. It is vital that the right location is chosen, which is why the final two options, Options A and C, are being assessed in detail. Work led by Highways England is currently underway to determine where and how best to tie in a new crossing to the existing road network. This work is expected to lead to public consultation on a proposed solution in late 2015 or early 2016.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2015-07-22T10:30:18.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389200/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389200/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389200/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-13","River Thames: Bridges","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what progress has been made regarding the new Lower Thames Crossing.","false","Biography information for Lord Hanningfield",,"Lord Hanningfield","HL1386"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389201","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-23","<p>We do not envisage any changes to plans for the Norwich – Liverpool line.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2015-07-23T16:24:53.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389201/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389201/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389201/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-13","East Anglia Railway Line","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government to what extent any plans for the Norwich–Liverpool line, particularly in the Chelmsford area, have been affected by recent changes to Network Rail.","false","Biography information for Lord Hanningfield",,"Lord Hanningfield","HL1387"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389202","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-27","<p>The Government has secured a deal that protects UK taxpayers from any risk from financing euro area bailouts now and in the future. This deal gives legal force to the commitment secured in 2010 that UK taxpayers would not be drawn into a euro area bailout. Under the European Financial Stability Mechanism (EFSM) short term financing agreement concluded on Friday 17 July, Greece’s IMF arrears have also been cleared.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley",,"2015-07-27T15:56:58.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389202/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389202/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389202/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-07-13","Loans: Greece","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether the United Kingdom will incur any financial costs relating to the bailout being given to the government of Greece, either through the European Central Bank or the International Monetary Fund, or in any other way.","false","Biography information for Lord Stoddart of Swindon",,"Lord Stoddart of Swindon","HL1388"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389203","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-07-17","<p>The £3 billion per year figure relates to the management of the UK’s civil nuclear liability and arises from historic and current nuclear operations. Sellafield, the UK’s largest, most complex and challenging site, accounts for £1.9 billion per year of this cost. The best estimate for clean-up costs for the UK’s earliest nuclear sites over a 100 year plus programme is set out in the Nuclear Provision which together with the Nuclear Decommissioning Authority’s (NDA) anticipated costs and expenditure, budget and lifetime financials per site, is made publicly available via the NDA’s website (<a href="http://www.nda.gov.uk/" target="_blank">www.nda.gov.uk</a>).</p><p>Operators of new nuclear power stations are required by law to make prudent provision for their decommissioning, waste management and waste disposal costs. These costs are taken into account in the cost per MWh of electricity generated by new nuclear power stations.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"2015-07-17T10:32:58.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389203/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389203/answer","nuclear-provision-explaining-the-cost-of-Britains-nuclear-clean-up-2015.pdf","nuclear-provision-explaining-the-cost-of-Britains-nuclear-clean-up-2015.pdf","Nuclear-provision-explaining-the-costs","Nuclear-provision-explaining-the-costs","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389203/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-07-13","Nuclear Power","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the answer by Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth on 8 July (HL Deb, col 177–180) concerning the annual cost of £3 billion of storing and protecting the United Kingdom’s civil nuclear legacy, whether they will provide details of such costs; and whether they are taken into account when stating the cost per megawatt hour of electricity from nuclear power stations.","false","Biography information for Lord Stoddart of Swindon",,"Lord Stoddart of Swindon","HL1389"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389204","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-07-22","<p>The water industry in England and Wales was privatised in 1989, when the ten publicly-owned regional water authorities transferred their functions and assets to private water companies. There are currently 32 privately-owned water companies serving England and Wales, overseen by the independent economic regulator Ofwat.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As an appointed water and sewerage company, Thames Water’s licence of appointment specifies a specific area of appointment. Water company licencing is a matter for Ofwat. The Government has therefore made no assessment of any such change in the company’s structure.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><br></p><p> </p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble",,"2015-07-22T16:47:14.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389204/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389204/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389204/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-07-13","Thames Water","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the case for dividing Thames Water into two new companies, one with responsibility for the upper Thames area and one with responsibility for London and the lower Thames area.","false","Biography information for Lord Stoddart of Swindon",,"Lord Stoddart of Swindon","HL1390"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389205","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-27","<p>The EU budget mechanisms, which determine the UK's net contribution to the EU‎ from 2014-20, were agreed in 2013, when the Prime Minister secured an historic real terms cut to expenditure and protected the rebate. This House approved that deal on 8 July 2015.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley",,"2015-07-27T15:56:17.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389205/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389205/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389205/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-07-13","EU Budget: Contributions","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what plans they have to renegotiate the funding of the European Union budget so that the United Kingdom’s contribution does not increase as a result of economic success.","false","Biography information for Lord Stoddart of Swindon",,"Lord Stoddart of Swindon","HL1391"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389206","Cabinet Office","false","2015-07-21","<p>Ministers regularly meet with the Charity Commission to discuss the legal and regulatory framework for charities in England and Wales. Charities are already required to provide information relating to income sources, senior staff remuneration, and the number of employed staff in their annual accounts and trustees’ annual reports. The accounts and reports of registered charities with an annual income of over £25,000 are publicly available from the Charity Commission at <a href="http://www.gov.uk/" target="_blank">www.gov.uk</a>.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley",,"2015-07-21T14:05:25.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389206/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389206/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389206/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-07-13","Charities","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they intend to discuss with the Charity Commission the need for charities to include in their requests for donations the level of support they receive from the Government and other public bodies; the salaries paid to the Chief Executive Officer and other senior staff; and the number of full-time and part-time paid staff employed.","false","Biography information for Lord Stoddart of Swindon",,"Lord Stoddart of Swindon","HL1392"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389207","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-24","<p>The legal and moral responsibility to pay pensions to former Rhodesian and Zimbabwean public servants sits with the Government of Zimbabwe. The British Government continues to remind the relevant authorities in Zimbabwe of this legal commitment. Following our most recent approach the Government of Zimbabwe wrote to us on 27 May. They explained that pension repayments remain affected by current financial constraints in Zimbabwe and the state of the wider economy. Nonetheless, at our prompting they committed to continuing to seek a solution.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-07-24T11:28:25.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389207/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389207/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389207/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-13","Zimbabwe: Pensions","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they plan to use overseas superannuation funds to pay pensioners owed money by the government of Zimbabwe; and, if so, when they will do so.","false","Biography information for Lord Goodlad",,"Lord Goodlad","HL1393"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389208","Home Office","false","2015-07-22","<p>The Home Office does not hold the information requested. The closest available data relates to Certificates of Sponsorship used in visa applications, and is given in the table below.</p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="6"><p><strong>Table cs_03: Applicants for visas for work using sponsorship certificates: Human Health and Social Work Activities</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td> </td><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>2014</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Tier 2</p></td><td><p>2,915</p></td><td><p>1,565</p></td><td><p>1,586</p></td><td><p>2,114</p></td><td><p>3,121</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Tier 5</p></td><td><p>1,024</p></td><td><p>1,196</p></td><td><p>1,020</p></td><td><p>1,182</p></td><td><p>1,290</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: Immigration Statistics January-March 2015</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2015-07-22T12:39:10.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389208/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389208/answer","PQHL1394 Table 15.07.15[1].docx","PQHL1394 Table 15.07.15[1].docx","Table - PQ HL1394 ","Table - PQ HL1394 ","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389208/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-07-13","NHS: Migrant Workers","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many visas have been issued to (1) doctors, and (2) nurses, for employment in the National Health Service in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Lord Green of Deddington",,"Lord Green of Deddington","HL1394"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389209","Cabinet Office","false","2015-07-27","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have attached a copy of the Authority's response.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley",,"2015-07-27T15:43:17.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389209/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389209/answer","UKSA HL1395.pdf","UKSA HL1395.pdf","UK Statistics Reply ","UK Statistics Reply ","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389209/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-07-13","Construction: Statistics","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they plan to ask the Office for National Statistics to review the validity of the input data for the construction industry statistical bulletin published in May, in the light of the recent amendments made to their findings.","false","Biography information for Lord Naseby",,"Lord Naseby","HL1395"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389210","Department of Health","false","2015-07-16","<p>The March 2013 national Agenda for Change collective agreement sets out the respective responsibilities between staff and employers on workforce re-profiling and can be found on the NHS Employers website at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.nhsemployers.org/your-workforce/pay-and-reward/pay/agenda-for-change-pay/agenda-for-change-amendments-2013" target="_blank">http://www.nhsemployers.org/your-workforce/pay-and-reward/pay/agenda-for-change-pay/agenda-for-change-amendments-2013</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>There are no plans to review how job responsibilities will be evaluated.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-07-16T16:46:48.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389210/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389210/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389210/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-13","NHS: Career Development","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether he plans to review responsibilities within pay bands in the NHS; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Liz McInnes","Heywood and Middleton","Liz McInnes","6816"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389211","Home Office","false","2015-07-20","<p>Following an independent review, we fundamentally revised the Prevent strategy in 2011.</p><p>As part of CONTEST performance management we monitor work under the strategy and report on it annually through the CONTEST Annual report.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2015-07-20T10:23:16.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389211/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389211/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389211/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-07-13","Counter-terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will instigate an independent review of the performance of the Prevent strategy.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","6772"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389212","Home Office","false","2015-07-17","<p>The Impact Assessment to the Psychoactive Substances Bill gives estimated costs of enforcement on the criminal justice system. Existing resources are already being used by the police and trading standards officers to tackle the supply of new psychoactive substances using legislation not specifically designed for this purpose.</p><p>The Impact Assessment anticipates that, once the Bill is enacted, very few establishments will continue to sell psychoactive substances, so the total enforcement costs are expected to be minimal. This follows the experience of Ireland which enacted a similar bill.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-07-17T11:03:28.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389212/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389212/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389212/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-07-13","Police: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 7 July 2015 to Question 5856, what the additional costs attached to the enforcement of the new legislation are expected to be.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","6773"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389213","Home Office","false","2015-07-20","<p>For security reasons we do not publish a breakdown of the counter-terrorism policing budget by region or capability.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2015-07-20T10:24:47.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389213/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389213/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389213/answer","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389213/answer/previousversion/15384","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-07-13","Counter-terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans she has to increase the number of counter-terrorism officers stationed abroad.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","6875"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389214","Home Office","false","2015-07-17","<p>As described in the Crime and Courts Act 2013 , the National Crime Agency (NCA) is responsible for a criminal intelligence function that includes analysing and disseminating information relevant to combating serious and organised crime.</p><p>It is for them to decide what information is included in assessments of the threat from serious and organised crime.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2015-07-17T10:39:06.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389214/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389214/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389214/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-07-13","Offences against Children: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 23 June 2015 to Question 3680, if she will ask the National Crime Agency to estimate the number of women who pose a potential risk of being a child abuser or of seeking out child sex images online.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","6864"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389215","Home Office","false","2015-07-17","<p>The United Kingdom has some of the strongest protections in the world to safeguard women and girls. The Government is committed to further supporting women to rebuild their lives, to breaking cycles of abuse and bringing perpetrators to justice.</p><p>We will continue to update our Violence Against Women and Girls strategy, as we have done every year, and will consider the Special Rapporteur's findings.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2015-07-17T10:24:57.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389215/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389215/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389215/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-07-13","Crimes of Violence: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she is taking to meet the recommendations set out in the UK report by the UN Special Rapporteur on Violence against Women.","false","Biography information for Michael Dugher","Barnsley East","Michael Dugher","6869"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389216","Home Office","false","2015-08-07","<p>As stated in the last PQ response (Q 3489), 82 asylum claims were made of which 52 were subsequently granted asylum.</p><p>Of the remaining 30, 10 have been removed following the refusal of their claim and 2 have had their appeals allowed. The remainder have outstanding appeals or applications or are subject to ongoing enforcement action or investigation.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-08-07T11:51:10.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389216/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389216/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389216/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-07-13","Immigration: Olympic Games 2012","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 30 June 2015 to Question 3489, on immigration: Olympic Games 2012, what the immigration status is of the 30 people who made a claim for asylum which has not been granted; and what enforcement action has been taken in each such case.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","6885"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389217","Home Office","false","2015-07-17","<p>Work was done in 1997 and 2003 to take DNA from prisoners who were imprisoned before DNA samples were routinely taken on arrest.</p><p>If the police follow standard practice consistently, then subsequent prisoners’ DNA profiles are on the database because they were taken on arrest. So it is not necessary to take prisoners’ DNA now.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-07-17T11:07:58.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389217/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389217/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389217/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-07-13","DNA: Databases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 23 June 2015 to Question 3770, if she will take steps to ensure that the DNA profiles of prisoners who have been imprisoned since before DNA profiles were taken on arrest are on the DNA database.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","6878"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389218","Home Office","false","2015-07-21","<p>We continue to take action against individuals linked to the ETS English Language test fraud. We will not project timeframes for conclusion of that action as this will be dependent on a range of factors including the resolution of associated litigation and appeals.</p><p>Data on the operational response to the abuse of Secure English Language Testing is published quarterly in the Home Office Transparency data which can be accessed at: www.gov.uk/government/publications/temporary-and-permanent-migration-data-may-2015.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-07-21T13:02:17.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389218/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389218/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389218/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-07-13","Immigrants: English Language","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 29 June 2015 to Question 3767, what estimate she has made of the likely time it will take enforcement action against the remaining individuals who have been identified as having participated in English language test fraud; and what estimate she has made of the number of removals that will result from such action.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","6879"
